<L>__{exterior cane fields day}
<A>__{an overseer is explaining to the new slaves solomon among them how to cultivate cane. with a knife in hand he demonstrates the process:}
<C>__{overseer}
<D>__{draw the cane from the rick, cut the top and flags from the stalk, understand? leave only that part which is sound and healthy. cast off the rest...}
<L>__{exterior cane fields day}
<A>__{ november, 1846 about thirty slaves are working the field. they are divided into three gangs. the first which draw the cane, the next lay the cane in the drill, the last then hoe the rows after. solomon is among a gang that draws and cuts, and he moves with speed and skill. certainly more so than he displayed picking cotton. standing with his overseer, judge turner watches.}
